name: 2-formylbenzeneboronic acid

The boronic acid group (-B(OH)2) is capable of forming intermolecular hydrogen bonds, which significantly increases the melting point. We could predict this to add approximately another +70°C. Combining these contributions, our estimated melting point should be the sum of the increments plus the melting point of benzene.
